      • backgroundThreadRunMethod

        protected void backgroundThreadRunMethod()
        This is the method that is called by the Thread.run() instance in the background thread created and started in AbstractBlockingStreamingIterator.start(). Please set up and start the items being iterated over. Make sure to call AbstractBlockingStreamingIterator.blockingPut(Object) when appropriate. Any uncaught exceptions will be thrown by the thread using the iterator the next time AbstractBlockingStreamingIterator.next() or AbstractBlockingStreamingIterator.hasNext() is used.

        backgroundThreadRunMethod in class AbstractBlockingStreamingIterator<String>
